Six people have died in a crash involving a sedan and a truck on the N11 road between Loskop dam and Middelburg in Mpumalanga, on Monday night. Mpumalanga Community Safety spokesperson Moeti Mmusi says all the deceased were occupants of the sedan. The cause of the crash is being investigating. “The six were all occupants of the sedan, and they all perished at the scene. They include a toddler, the driver and all passengers [of the sedan]. The cause of the crash is unclear at this stage. The probe has been instituted,” adds Mmusi.